    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES62-5A, ES62-5D, ES67-5A AND
        ES67-5D - REASSEMBLY - MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place 1st speed gear and a thrust washer on the shaft. Secure them with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301047">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301047" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301047" filename="../figg13/g1301047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Place 1st Speed Gear and Thrust Washer on Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safety glasses to prevent possible personal injury from flying metal pieces.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place Moly #2 lubricant on the shaft, then install the loose needle bearings around the
                shaft diameter (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301048">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301048" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301048" filename="../figg13/g1301048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Install Loose Needle Bearings Around Shaft Diameter</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the 2nd speed gear on the shaft. Install the 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear and secure it
                with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301049">Figure 49</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301049" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301049" filename="../figg13/g1301049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Install 2nd-3rd Speed Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the fluted shaft diameters with Moly #2 lubricant. Then install the 2nd-3rd speed
                synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301050">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301050" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301050" filename="../figg13/g1301050.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Install 2nd-3rd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place Moly #2 lubricant on the fluted diameters. Then install 3rd speed gear and thrust
                washer on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301051">Figure 51</hotlnk>). Secure them with a snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301051" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301051" filename="../figg13/g1301051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Install 3rd Speed Gear and Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 4th speed gear and thrust washer on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301052">Figure 52</hotlnk>). Secure them with a snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301052" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301052" filename="../figg13/g1301052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Install 4th Speed Gear and Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place 4th-5th speed synchronizer on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301053">Figure 53</hotlnk>). Use a suitable driver to install the pocket bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301053" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301053" filename="../figg13/g1301053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Place 4th-5th Speed Synchronizer on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the mainshaft on the bench. Install 1st-reverse clutch gear, needle bearing, reverse
                gear, and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301054">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301054" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301054" filename="../figg13/g1301054.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Install 1st-Reverse Clutch Gear, Needle Bearing, Reverse Gear, and Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable driver to install the output bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301055">Figure 55</hotlnk>). This bearing must be firmly seated against the thrust
                washer to prevent the washer from moving.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301055" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301055" filename="../figg13/g1301055.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Install Output Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
